---
id: base-evaluator
name: Base Output Evaluator
version: 1.0.0
description: Base template for building LLM output evaluation prompts. Not intended for direct use — inherit from this to create domain-specific evaluators for your test suites.
parameters:
  - name: llm_output
    type: string
    required: true
    description: "The LLM-generated output to evaluate"
  - name: original_prompt
    type: string
    required: true
    description: "The prompt that produced the output being evaluated"
  - name: evaluation_criteria
    type: json
    required: true
    description: "[{'name': <name>, 'description': <description>, 'weight': <weight>},{'name': <name>, 'description': <description>, 'weight': <weight>}]"
  - name: reference_output
    type: string
    required: false
    description: "Optional gold-standard reference output for comparison"
  - name: scoring_scale
    type: integer
    required: false
    default: 5
    min: 2
    max: 10
    description: "Maximum score per criterion (e.g. 5 = score each criterion 1-5)"
system: "../systems/evaluator.md"
---
# Context
## Evaluation Criteria

{% set jsonCriteria = evaluation_criteria %}
{% for criterion in jsonCriteria %}
 - {{ criterion.name }} (weight: {{ criterion.weight }}): {{ criterion.description }}
{% endfor %}

{% if reference_output %}
## Reference Output
The following is considered the target quality level:
```
{{ reference_output }}
```

{% endif %}

## Output Schema
```json
{
  "overall_score": <float, weighted average normalized to 0.0-1.0>,
  "pass": <boolean, true if overall_score >= 0.7>,
  "criteria_scores": [
    {
      "criterion": "<name>",
      "score": <int, 1-{{ scoring_scale }}>,
      "max_score": {{ scoring_scale }},
      "weight": <float>,
      "rationale": "<2-3 sentence justification for this score>"
    }
  ],
  "strengths": ["<notable positive aspects>"],
  "weaknesses": ["<specific areas of failure or improvement>"],
  "recommendation": "pass" | "revise" | "reject"
}
```

# User
Evaluate the following LLM output. Return ONLY the JSON evaluation.

## Original Prompt
```
{{ original_prompt }}
```

## Output to Evaluate
```
{{ llm_output }}
```
